description:
A Map by Lcarroli

My father kept a photographic record of his life as a rigger and linesman with Electric Power Transmission. These are his personal photographs from various transmission line projects around Australia (and one from Italy) in the period 1955 to 1974. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;

Migrant workers, in photographic and historical records, are often unnamed and anonymous. My father wrote place names, dates and voltage on many of the photographs. English wasn't his first language so many of the place names are incorrectly spelled.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;

This map includes photographs and sound recordings. However, please note that the map markers indicate towns not specific addresses. So please adjust the map zoom when you link into places.&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;

A blog - &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;http://transmissionlines.blogspot.com&amp;quot;&amp;gt;http://transmissionlines.blogspot.com&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; - brings together a number of recombinant content sharing and social networking efforts to archive and present this story. Pieces of the documentation can be accessed via Blogger, Flickr, Platial, Slide and Facebook. You can subscribe to RSS feeds to keep up to date with the work as it evolves. Where possible, I have also linked to Picture Australia searches from some of the map postings. &amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;

Transmission Lines 1955 - 1974 is a project by Linda Carroli.
